commText: Jaiswal and Buttler are at the crease. Jaiswal is on strike. Bhuvneshwar will open the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, 1 run, short of length angled across, Jaiswal rides the bounce and punches it square of the wicket
Bhuvneshwar to Buttler, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bhuvneshwar to Buttler, out Caught by Marco Jansen!! Wow! Bhuvi strikes with his second ball. Buttler comes in and departs first ball. Bhuvi had the upper hand in this match-up and he has won that battle. Buttler cannot believe it, he tosses his bat up, catches it and walks away. Back of a length delivery and it swings in, Buttler looks to force it through the off-side and gets a thick outside edge, the ball flies to the wide slip fielder and Jansen takes it nonchalantly. That ball was traveling but Jansen just gobbled it into his bucket hands. Buttler c Marco Jansen b Bhuvneshwar 0(1)
Buttler vs Bhuvneshwar in T20s 92 balls 104 runs 7 dismissals Avg 14.85 SR 113
Sanju Samson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bhuvneshwar to Samson, no run, I0$ back of a length and angling in, Samson turns it with soft hands to mid-wicket
Bhuvneshwar to Samson, no run, I0$ fullish outswinger, Samson lifts his bat and lets it go
Bhuvneshwar to Samson, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Bhuvneshwar to Samson, out Bowled!! Cleaned up! Where has this Bhuvi been? This is the Bhuvi of old. This is Bhuvi we all remember. This is the Bhuvi who is swinging the ball and beating the batters. The inswinger and it keeps coming in, Samson looks to drive through the line as the length was fuller, but the ball sneaks past inside edge, brushes the pad and rattles the middle-stump. What a start for SRH! Buttler and Samson back in the hut within the first over. Samson b Bhuvneshwar 0(3)
Riyan Parag, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bhuvneshwar to Riyan Parag, no run, I0$ swinging into the right hander, Parag does not move his feet but manages to turn it to mid-on
Marco Jansen, comes into the attack
Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, no run, I0$ fullish delivery and Jaiswal is not convincing with his drive, chips it tamely in front of mid-off
Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, no run, on a length and outside off, Jaiswal pushes it on the rise and picks out cover
Slip for Jansen as well

Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, FOUR, I0$ short of length delivery and Jaiswal is rushed on the pull, gets it a lot straighter than he would have liked but clears the infield comfortably and picks up his first boundary
Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, 1 run, I0$ angled into the pads, Jaiswal clips it through square leg
Marco Jansen to Riyan Parag, no run, I0$ slanted across the right hander, Parag shoulders arms
Marco Jansen to Riyan Parag, no run, short ball angled across, Parag takes it on and is beaten by Jansen's extra bounce
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, no run, back of a length around off, Jaiswal lifts his bat and lets it go
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, 1 run, back of a length close to off, Jaiswal steers to short third where Unadkat makes a good stop
Bhuvneshwar to Riyan Parag, FOUR, in the air and over cover. Full and swinging away, Parag commits to the drive and does not bother to keep it down, he goes up and over the fielder

Bhuvneshwar to Riyan Parag, SIX, whoa! Now expects the inswinger and is ready for it, does not plant his front foot across and that gives him the chance to have a free swing of the hands, lofts it with the swing and sends it sailing over wide long-on
Bhuvneshwar to Riyan Parag, no run, low full toss on off, Parag brings his bat down and eases it to mid-off

Bhuvneshwar to Riyan Parag, FOUR, shot! Slower delivery outside off, not quite on the driveable length but Parag goes through with the shot, rolls his wrists over and places it in front of square on the off-side

Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, no run, dropped! Would you believe it! The skipper of all the people has put down a regulation catch. Full pitcher around off and Jaiswal goes hard on the drive, hits it uppishly to mid-off and Cummins makes a mess. It went around his mid-riff and burst through his hands, hits his tummy and goes to ground
Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, 2 runs, short of length delivery and Jaiswal is once again hurried on the pull, miscues it towards the mid-wicket region and picks up a brace
Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, no ball, 1 run, low full toss around off, Jaiswal jams it towards short third and crosses over. Jansen has overstepped
Free-hit coming up

Marco Jansen to Riyan Parag, no ball, goes round the wicket and sprays it down leg, no chance for Parag to make any sort of connection and Klaasen has to dive to glove the ball. In fact, Jansen has overstepped again.. The free-hit would have stayed anyway
Marco Jansen to Riyan Parag, 1 run, nails it close to yorker length and Parag can only dig it out to long-on
Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, no run, another one in the blockhole, Jaiswal jams it to the right of Jansen

Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, FOUR, short of length delivery and Jaiswal gets hold of this one, he gets into position and nails the pull in front of square. There was a fielder in the deep and he placed it wide of him

Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, FOUR, lovely shot! Jansen goes for the yorker outside off, got it almost right as well but Jaiswal bends down, opens the bat face and squeezes it behind square on the off-side
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Cummins to Riyan Parag, 1 run, I0$ full delivery on the pads, Parag flicks to deep square leg
Round the wicket to Jaiswal

Cummins to Jaiswal, FOUR, back of a length around off, Jaiswal stays leg-side and that gives him space to free his hands, punches it in front of square and the ball races through the extra cover region

Cummins to Jaiswal, FOUR, fuller and outside off, Jaiswal takes the aerial route and goes over the cover region. Not quite off the middle but he cleared the infield with ease and beat Unadkat near sweeper cover
Cummins to Jaiswal, no run, 149.4ks full and close to yorker range, Jaiswal digs it out to mid-off

Cummins to Jaiswal, SIX, massive hit! Wrong line from Cummins - short but angled down leg, Jaiswal stays inside the line and hooks it over fine leg. That was bowled at 150.4ks but the ball went quicker off the bat
Cummins to Jaiswal, no run, backs away and Cummins follows him with a yorker, Jaiswal jams it back to the bowler

Overs summary (1-5) -> Bhuvneshwar Kumar strikes early, Buttler is out for a golden duck -> Samson departs for a duck, he's bowled by a terrific Bhuvi inswinger -> Jaiswal living a charmed life, Cummins drops his catch -> Jansen bowls an expensive over, concedes 14 runs in it -> 50 up for Rajasthan in the 5th over, Jaiswal on the charge
T Natarajan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, no run, in the air and safe. On a length and outside off, Parag drives uppishly and the ball lands in front of mid-off

T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, FOUR, this is counterattack at its best. Natarajan misses his yorker and feeds a full delivery, right in the slot for Parag and he goes through with the loft, clears mid-off and picks up a one bounce four
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, FOUR, good length ball on off, Parag stays leg-side and chips it straight back over the bowler. Not quite off the middle but enough to beat the long-off fielder
Natarajan goes round the wicket
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, no run, slower ball bowled into the wicket, Parag charges down and is deceived by the lack of pace, misses his shot and the ball lobs over off-stump

T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, no run, dropped! Tough chance and Abhishek cannot hold on. Full and outside off, Parag drills the drive straight to extra cover and the ball was traveling, Abhishek got both his hands but the ball does not stick. In fact it seemed easier on replays and he made a hash of it
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, wide, slower bouncer, Parag ducks under and collects the wide
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, 1 run, off-pace back of a length delivery, Parag turns it to long-on and retains strike

Timeout! Bhuvi provided a dream start for SRH by removing Buttler and Samson in the very first over. But these two have since counterattacked and kept up with the asking rate. Batting seems to have become easier and Rajasthan will fancy this with this pair striking the ball cleanly. SRH need to keep picking wickets
Jaydev Unadkat, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Unadkat to Riyan Parag, 1 run, on a length around middle and leg, worked through square leg with soft hands
Unadkat to Jaiswal, 1 run, pitched up by the bowler, Jaiswal drives it to long-on for a single
Unadkat to Riyan Parag, 1 run, slower delivery as Riyan Parag nudges it through mid-wicket for a single with soft hands
Unadkat to Jaiswal, 2 runs, on the shorter side, Jaiswal pulls it towards deep mid-wicket along the carpet, a couple of runs taken
Jaiswal gets distracted by the spidercam and backs off at the last moment. Klaasen and Unadkat are not happy as the latter had already delivered the ball
Unadkat to Jaiswal, 1 run, nudged to long-on by Jaiswal for a single
Unadkat to Riyan Parag, wide, banged in short by Unadkat as the ball sails over Riyan Parag's head
Unadkat to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, played through the off-side by Riyan Parag for a couple of runs to end the over
Nitish Reddy, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Nitish Reddy to Jaiswal, FOUR, fraction short outside off, Jaiswal rocks back and goes for a cut, gets an outside edge past the fielder at short third man. Moves to 40* with the help of that boundary
Nitish Reddy to Jaiswal, 2 runs, short and wide outside off, Jaiswal cuts it towards deep point and a misfield by Shahbaz near the boundary results in the second
Nitish Reddy to Jaiswal, 2 runs, pulls the short ball towards deep mid-wicket where Abhishek Sharma stops it with a dive
Nitish Reddy to Jaiswal, 1 run, on a length around middle and leg, nudged to long-on for a single
Nitish Reddy to Riyan Parag, wide, goes short as the ball sails over Riyan Parag's head, called a wide
Nitish Reddy to Riyan Parag, no run, back of a length on middle and leg, nudged back to Nitish Reddy
Nitish Reddy to Riyan Parag, wide, another short ball that sails over the batter's head, wide called again. Reviewed by the bowling team but it won't make a difference, still a wide
Nitish Reddy to Riyan Parag, 1 run, played through mid-wicket for a single to end the over
Pat Cummins [1.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to Riyan Parag, no run, flicked the overpitched delivery to the fielder at mid-wicket
Cummins to Riyan Parag, SIX, short and punished. Rocks back and pulls the short ball over deep square leg for half-a-dozen. Clean strike by Riyan Parag!
Cummins to Riyan Parag, 1 run, slower one by Cummins as Riyan Parag whips it towards deep mid-wicket for a single
Cummins to Jaiswal, no run, excellent yorker, right at the stumps as Jaiswal manages to dig it out
Cummins to Jaiswal, 2 runs, pitched up by the bowler on off, Jaiswal drives it through cover for a couple of runs
Cummins to Jaiswal, no run, short in length, Jaiswal goes for a pull, doesn't middle it through
Marco Jansen [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Marco Jansen to Riyan Parag, no run, on a length around middle and leg, nudged to mid-wicket by Riyan Parag
Marco Jansen to Riyan Parag, FOUR, short and wide outside off, Riyan Parag makes room and slashes this over backward point for a rollicking boundary
Marco Jansen to Riyan Parag, FOUR, short ball on leg, Riyan Parag plays it with soft hands, glancing it away to the fine leg fence, back-to-back boundaries for RP
Marco Jansen to Riyan Parag, no run, on a length around off, Riyan Parag guides it back to the bowler
Marco Jansen to Riyan Parag, 1 run, low full toss on middle and leg, driven along the carpet to long-on
Marco Jansen to Jaiswal, 1 run, yorker length ball that has been squeezed to long-on by Jaiswal

Overs summary (6-10) -> Abhishek drops Parag, Natarjan the unlucky bowler -> Unadkat bowls a boundaryless over -> Nitish Reddy comes on and concedes 12 runs -> Parag smashes Cummins for a six, but just 9 from the over -> Jansen is hit for consecutive fours by Parag
Shahbaz Ahmed, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Jaiswal, FOUR, fifty for Jaiswal! Short and wide outside off, Jaiswal smashes it towards deep cover as a misfield in the deep results in four runs. RR need 98 runs in 59 balls
Shahbaz Ahmed to Jaiswal, 2 runs, goes for a reverse hit, but gets an inside edge. The keeper can't gather it as they take a couple of runs
Shahbaz Ahmed to Jaiswal, 1 run, short and wide outside off, cut through point for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Riyan Parag, no run, full and straight outside off, Riyan Parag swings and misses
Shahbaz Ahmed to Riyan Parag, FOUR, fifty for Riyan Parag! Goes down on his knee and reverse sweeps this over backward point, enough elevation to clear the fielder inside the ring
Run-out appeal taken upstairs!
Shahbaz Ahmed to Riyan Parag, no run, drills this back to the bowler as Shahbaz Ahmed gets his hands to it and the ball hits the stumps at his end but Jaiswal was inside. He's safe!
T Natarajan [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Jaiswal, 1 run, yorker length ball on off, Jaiswal squeezes it into the off-side
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, 1 run, on a length around off, punched along the carpet to long-off for a single
T Natarajan to Jaiswal, 1 run, banged in short as Jaiswal pulls it through mid-wicket for a single
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, wide, on the shorter side as the ball sails over Riyan Parag's head
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, 1 run, low full toss on off, Riyan Parag drives it to cover where a misfield results in a single
T Natarajan to Jaiswal, 1 run, nicely executed yorker, Jaiswal squeezes it to mid-on for a single
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, 1 run, on the shorter side, pulled through mid-wicket for a single
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [2.0-0-16-2] is back into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Riyan Parag, 1 run, an inswinging delivery that has been whipped through mid-wicket by Riyan Parag
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, SIX, fantastic shot. A low full toss by Bhuvneshwar, Jaiswal goes down on his knee and swipes the juicy delivery over deep backward square leg for half-a-dozen
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, 1 run, on the fuller side, almost a yorker, Jaiswal squeezes it to long-on for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Riyan Parag, FOUR, runs coming thick and fast, what a partnership this is proving to be. Short in length around off, Riyan Parag smashes it towards wide long-off for a cracking four
Bhuvneshwar to Riyan Parag, 1 run, low full toss on middle and leg, clipped through square leg for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Jaiswal, 1 run, on the shorter side, Jaiswal slaps it over the infield at cover for a single
Timeout! RR in control as they require only 70 runs in 7 overs. With 8 wickets remaining they should be able to chase this down..
T Natarajan to Jaiswal, 1 run, short ball on leg, Jaiswal pulls it through backward square leg for a single
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, wide, attempted slower delivery but way outside off, a wide called
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, 1 run, short ball on off, Riyan Parag slaps it to long-off for a single
T Natarajan to Jaiswal, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

T Natarajan to Jaiswal, out Bowled!! Similar to the way Head got out. Too many similarities between the two innings. Head got out playing while playing such a shot, Jaiswal too gets out playing the same shot. Deja Vu. Guess both - Head and Jaiswal were dropped once each as well. For SRH, their number 4 Nitish Reddy played an impactful knock, for RR - Parag is doing the same. Was a low full toss and Jaiswal played it on to the stumps as he tried to play the scoop shot. Jaiswal b T Natarajan 67(40) [4s-7 6s-2]
Shimron Hetmyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
T Natarajan to Hetmyer, 1 run, low full toss that has been driven to long-on for a single
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, SIX, short and punished. Riyan Parag gets into position quickly and hammers the pull over deep mid-wicket for a flat six
T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, 1 run, slashed through the off-side for a single by Riyan Parag
Jaydev Unadkat [1.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack
Unadkat to Riyan Parag, no run, slower delivery outside off, just inside the tramline, left alone
Unadkat to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, played towards wide long-on for a couple of runs
Unadkat to Riyan Parag, SIX, stand and deliver. On a length and Riyan Parag has whipped it over long-on as he just clears the fielder. 150 up for RR
Unadkat to Riyan Parag, no run, yorker length delivery on off, Riyan Parag squeezes towards cover
Unadkat to Riyan Parag, wide, slower delivery attempted but it's a wide ball
Unadkat to Riyan Parag, 1 run, short and slow outside off, Riyan Parag cuts it through the off-side for a single
Unadkat to Hetmyer, FOUR, pitched up by the bowler, right in the slot as Hetmyer whips it over the non-striker for four runs. RR in cruise control

Overs summary (11-15) -> Jaiswal and Parag reach fifty in the same over (11) -> Bhuvi comes back and is taken for 14 runs -> Natarajan breaks the partnership, Jaiswall falls for 67 -> Parag keeps the sixes coming for RR
Pat Cummins [2.0-0-24-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to Riyan Parag, no run, low full toss as Riyan Parag clips it to short fine leg
Cummins to Riyan Parag, 1 run, swings early as the inside edge rolls towards short fine leg for a single
Cummins to Hetmyer, no run, slower delivery on off, Hetmyer is early to play his pull, gets beaten due to the lack of pace
Cummins to Hetmyer, 1 run, yorker length ball as Hetmyer digs it towards long-on for a single
Cummins to Riyan Parag, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Marco Jansen!! Pitched up by Cummins, right into the slot and Riyan Parag whips it straight to the fielder at long-on. Jansen doesn't miss out. Riyan Parag walks back after playing a fine knock. Riyan Parag c Marco Jansen b Cummins 77(49) [4s-8 6s-4]
Rovman Powell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Cummins to Powell, 1 run, played towards wide long-on by Powell for a single
Marco Jansen [3.0-0-29-0] is back into the attack
Marco Jansen to Powell, 2 wides, attempts a yorker but misses the line, down the leg-side as the keeper can't gather it cleanly either
Marco Jansen to Hetmyer, 1 run, yorker length ball that has been drilled to long-on for a single
Marco Jansen to Powell, wide, goes way too wide outside off and it's a wide ball
Marco Jansen to Powell, FOUR, pitched up by the bowler as Powell smashes it past the bowler for four runs. Umpire was quick enough to get out of its way
Marco Jansen to Powell, 2 runs, low full toss on leg, clipped through the leg-side for a couple of runs
Marco Jansen to Powell, wide, way too wide outside off, an extra run
Marco Jansen to Powell, FOUR, edged away to the fence. On a length outside off, Powell swings across the line, the outside edge flies past the keeper and that's four runs
Marco Jansen to Powell, no run, yorker length ball on middle and leg, Powell looks to work across the line, gets a leading edge to the off-side
Marco Jansen to Powell, no run, slower length ball outside off, Powell gets beaten on his cut
T Natarajan [3.0-0-28-1] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Hetmyer, SIX, tad slower, right into the slot, Hetmyer shimmies down and launches it over long-on for a clean six. No need to run for those
T Natarajan to Hetmyer, no run, short and slow outside off, Hetmyer gets an underedge towards the keeper
T Natarajan to Hetmyer, no run, yorker length ball on leg, Hetmyer squeezes it back to the bowler
T Natarajan to Hetmyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

T Natarajan to Hetmyer, out Caught by Marco Jansen!! Natarajan gets another wicket, only to make this game further interesting. Was a full toss and Hetmyer lofted it straight to the fielder at long-on. Jander might have struggled with the ball tonight but he has at least taken some decent catches. Hetmyer c Marco Jansen b T Natarajan 13(9) [4s-1 6s-1]
Dhruv Jurel, right handed bat, comes to the crease
T Natarajan to Dhruv Jurel, no run, short and wide outside off, Dhruv Jurel goes for a cut, gets an underedge towards the keeper
T Natarajan to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, chipped to wide long-on for a single as the bowler goes full
Two teams that have played some excellent cricket throughout the tournament. Up against each other. Are we in for a Super Over tonight?
Pat Cummins [3.0-0-27-1] is back into the attack
Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to Dhruv Jurel, out Caught by Abhishek Sharma!! Drifting on the pads, Dhruv Jurel flicks it straight to the fielder at deep square leg. Abhishek makes no mistake. Jurel departs without contributing much. Dhruv Jurel c Abhishek Sharma b Cummins 1(3)
Ravichandran Ashwin, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Cummins to Ashwin, 1 run, tad fuller on middle and leg, driven to long-on for a single
Cummins to Powell, no run, slower short ball outside off, Powell swings and misses
Cummins to Powell, no run, yorker length ball outside off, Powell gets beaten as he tries to squeeze it out
Cummins to Powell, no run, slower bouncer on off, Powell goes for a pull, connects thin air
Cummins to Powell, SIX, much needed for RR. This was pitched up outside off, right in the slot and Powell lofts it over deep extra cover for half-a-dozen. 13 runs required off 6 balls
Only four SRH fielders allowed outside the 30-yard circle due to slow over-rate!
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [3.0-0-30-2] is back into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Ashwin, 1 run, squeezed to long-on by Ashwin for a single. 12 runs needed in 5 balls... Super Over on the cards?
Bhuvneshwar to Powell, 2 runs, excellent yorker, right on the money as Powell squeezes it to long-on for a couple of runs
Equation: 10 runs required in 4 balls..
Bhuvneshwar to Powell, FOUR, brilliant shot. Keeps his cool and scoops this overpitched delivery towards fine leg for four runs does Powell. Only 6 runs required now..
Bhuvneshwar to Powell, 2 runs, they inch closer to victory. A low full tos on off, Powell drives it to long-off for a couple of runs more. RR need 4 runs in 2 balls
Run-out appeal taken upstairs!

Bhuvneshwar to Powell, 2 runs, Powell is safe! Flicks this low full toss towards deep square leg and calls for two. The throw from the deep is a flat and accurate one. The keeper takes off the bails in a jiffy, however, Powell makes it back in with a dive
Equations: 2 runs required in 1 ball. Super Over? Been a long time since we have had a Super Over...
Bhuvneshwar to Powell, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Bhuvneshwar to Powell, out Lbw!! What a thriller of a game folks! SRH win it. A full toss on leg, Powell looks to whip it away, however, gets hit on the pads. Struck on the back pad and the replays confirm this was hitting the leg-stump. Powell did review the onfield decision but he knew he was a goner and started to walk off even before the third umpire made the decision. Sunrisers Hyderabad win by 1 run. Superb comeback by Sunrisers after that Jaiswal and Parag partnership! Powell lbw b Bhuvneshwar 27(15) [4s-3 6s-1]

23:26 Local Time, 17:56 GMT, 23:26 IST: That's a remarkable comeback by SRH to clinch an impressive final ball victory after that brilliant partnership between Jaiswal and Parag. They did take two early wickets in the form of Buttler and Samson, however, Jaiswal and Parag had other plans tonight. Jaiswal was dropped by Cummins and the opener made sure that the opposition paid for their mistake. Jaiswal and Parag had an exceptional 134-run partnership, however, none of them were able to carry on and take their team over the line. SRH pacers were clinical at the death and although RR looked in cruise control, the hosts managed to snatch an exciting victory in the closing stages of the game. Stay around for the presentations..

Sanju Samson | RR captain: We have played some really close games this season, won a couple of them and lost this one. Credit to the SRH bowlers for the way they fought back. The margin of error is very less in the IPL. The game is never done till it is done. It was tough to bat against the new ball and when it got old, it became easier. Credit to both youngsters (Jaiswal and Parag), myself and Jos (Buttler) got out in the powerplay, they played well and got us to that position.

Travis Head: It's a good win, it's probably one that we didn't expect at the end there. Cummins and Bhuvi showed their class at the end and got us a nice win. We've been playing well, we've had a couple of losses, nice for the energy. It was challenging but with the wicket and the way Pat bowled the 19th over, he'd be disappointed with the last ball, but class at the end, two class players, two of the old boys. Very satisfied with the win. I thought that (201) was a great score. Nitish played out of his skin again. He's had a couple of innings now where's he's stepped up, made it look really easy. It was a tough pitch. I felt we had heaps but that's T20 crickets, it comes down to the wire most times. Always nice to win in front of your home fans.
SRH defending targets in IPL 2024 6 matches 5 wins 1 defeat
-- First defeat in a run chase for RR this season.

Narrowest margin of win for SRH in IPL (by runs) 1 run vs RR Hyderabad 2024 * 2 runs vs PK Mullanpur 2024 3 runs vs MI Mumbai WS 2022 4 runs vs DC Dubai 2014 4 runs vs RPS Vizag 2016 4 runs vs RCB Abu Dhabi 2021
Narrowest margin of defeat for RR in IPL (by runs) 1 run vs DC Delhi 2012 1 run vs SRH Hyderabad 2024 * 4 runs vs MI Brabourne 2010 4 runs vs DC Delhi 2018 4 runs vs PK Wankhede 2021
-- Rovman Powell wicket was Bhuvneshwar Kumar's first outside the Powerplay this season

Highest partnership in a losing run chase in IPL 135 K Williamson - M Pandey SRH v RCB Bengaluru 2018 134 Y Jaiswal - R Parag RR v SRH Hyderabad 2024 * 126 Faf du Plessis - G Maxwell RCB v CSK Bengaluru 2023
Stats by Deepu Narayanan

Cummins | SRH captain: I am good, was an amazing game. That's T20 cricket. Anything can happen, Bhuvi executed that last ball. You try to take some wickets in the middle. Natarajan is a good yorker bowler, fortunately we got some wickets. Played some games here, thought 200 could have been chased down. He (Nitish Reddy) sums up the conditions pretty well, he's amazing, great in the field, gives some overs with the ball as well.

Bhuvneshwar Kumar: I think that's my nature, I wasn't thinking much about the result in the last over. There was no discussion in the last over, was just focussed on the process. Was thinking just about bowling two good balls, anything could have happened. I wasn't thinking much, was just focussed on the process. The ball swung so much today, can't really pinpoint, really enjoyed bowling. Luckily got wickets today. When the season started my thought process was different but it changed when the batters played in such a way. My thought process changed completely to be honest (from the time the time the season started to today.)

Sunrisers Hyderabad get back to winning ways. They did lose a few games over the last few days but that's the nature of IPL. Rajasthan Royals have been on a roll since the inception of IPL 2024 and this is one of their rare defeats. Only a matter of three weeks more. Anything is possible from this point. Anyone can win, anyone can lose. That's how volatile this league has been! Get ready to be surprised and shocked over the next few weeks. That's all from our side folks. It's goodbye from Akshay, Abhinand, Nikhil and Siva. Good night!
